Date: 14/8/1920
Source: Grey River Argus
Author:
Vol / Page: 5
Edition:
Quote: When you read in the capitalist press, how this member or that member, gave the Labour Party Leader a severe slathering up, publishing verbatim reports of their speeches and finishing up, that Mr Holland "made a spirited reply["] it is easy to realise there is a conspiracy of silence and the general reader will not get the Labour Members' views unless the Labour people make it their business to place them before them.
